===Etymology===
{{rfscript|Gothic}}
{{etyl|enm}} {{term|trewe|trewe|loyal, faithful, firm, steadfast, adhering to the truth|lang=enm}} from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|treowe|trēowe|firm, loyal, trustworthy|lang=ang}} from {{proto|Germanic|trewwjaz|having good faith|lang=en}} from {{proto|Indo-European|dru-|tree|lang=en}} from {{proto|Indo-European|deru-|to be firm, solid|lang=en}}. Akin to {{etyl|ofs|-}} {{term|triuwi|triuwi|true, faithful|lang=ofs}} ({{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|getrouw|getrouw||lang=nl}}), {{etyl|goh|-}} {{term|gatriuwu|gatriuwu|faithful, loyal|lang=goh}} ({{etyl|de|-}} {{term|treu|treu||lang=de}} "faithful, true"), {{etyl|non|-}} {{term|tryggr|tryggr|faithful, true|lang=non}}, {{etyl|got|-}} {{term|triggws|triggws|faithful, trusty|lang=}}, {{ang}} {{term|treow|trēo, trēow|tree|lang=ang}}. More at [[tree]].

